PageV01P100
# @COMMENT: Passage not found in HSNX. Placement based on content. The reference to sharing water from a good well, might be an aside and is provisionally placed after the discussion of the wells of the Quraysh (HSNXV01P151A before the discussion of ʿAbd al-Muṭṭalib’s vow). Similar traditions are also found in WHAYA (QSHBV01P380A, SHBMV04P352A, HBHXV42P009C, IHMAV07P489D, and HJRTV17P752A), WSACD (HBHXV43P337A and HJRTV17P752A), and WJHZA (RHWXV02P566A, BNHXV11P331A, HYZXV01P278A, AAMZV03P082A, and HJRTV17P752A). The passage is an enignmatic tradition about the prohibition of withholding water from a well. @EC_06/19/23@

# @ZTKXV01P553A_BEG_WMFGH حدثنا ابن الأصبهاني قال أنا @TR1_MFGH@ محمد بن فضيل قال حدثنا محمد بن إسحاق عن محمد بن إبراهيم التميمي، عن سعيد بن المسيب عن معمر بن عبد الله قال سمعت النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم يقول لا يدخر إلا خاطئ قال وكان معمر يدخر. @ZTKXV01P553A_END_WMFGH
